ar rotate-45"}],"How do loans work?"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-dust text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3","children":["$","p",null,{"children":"A borrower creates an inscription specifying what they want to borrow (debt), what they offer as collateral, interest terms, and loan duration. Lenders browse available inscriptions and fill ones that match their criteria. The borrower's collateral is locked in a dedicated contract (locker) until the loan is repaid or expires. If the borrower doesn't repay within the duration, the lender can liquidate and claim the collateral."}]}]]}],"$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12"]}],null,"$L13"]}],{},null,false]},null,false]},null,false],"$L14",false]],"m":"$undefined","G":["$15",[]],"s":false,"S":true}
